A police officer arrested for allegedly sodomising a 15-year-old boy on Christmas Day has been arraigned in Kisumu. AP officer Nelson Cheruiyot of Critical Infrastructure Protection Unit was presented before senior resident magistrate Fatuma Rashid.Â He was charged with defilement. The court heard that on the night of December 25-26, 2020, in Shauri Moyo police line, Kisumu Central, Cheruiyot had anal sex with the Form 1 student. The cop was also charged with committing an indecent act with a child contrary to the law. He, however, pleaded not guilty to all the charges. The magistrate ruled that he be released on a Sh200,000 bond. The case will be mentioned on January 21, 2021, and heard on April 1, 2021.